To compute \(1201012_4 + 21321031_4\), we first need to convert these base-4 numbers to base-10.

### Conversion of \(1201012_4\) to base-10:

\[1201012_4\]

Each digit is multiplied by \(4\) raised to the power of its position, starting from 0 on the right:

\[1 \cdot 4^6 + 2 \cdot 4^5 + 0 \cdot 4^4 + 1 \cdot 4^3 + 0 \cdot 4^2 + 1 \cdot 4^1 + 2 \cdot 4^0\]

\[= 1 \cdot 4096 + 2 \cdot 1024 + 0 \cdot 256 + 1 \cdot 64 + 0 \cdot 16 + 1 \cdot 4 + 2 \cdot 1\]

\[= 4096 + 2048 + 0 + 64 + 0 + 4 + 2\]

\[= 6214_{10}\]

### Conversion of \(21321031_4\) to base-10:

\[21321031_4\]

Each digit is multiplied by \(4\) raised to the power of its position, starting from 0 on the right:

\[2 \cdot 4^7 + 1 \cdot 4^6 + 3 \cdot 4^5 + 2 \cdot 4^4 + 1 \cdot 4^3 + 0 \cdot 4^2 + 3 \cdot 4^1 + 1 \cdot 4^0\]

\[= 2 \cdot 16384 + 1 \cdot 4096 + 3 \cdot 1024 + 2 \cdot 256 + 1 \cdot 64 + 0 \cdot 16 + 3 \cdot 4 + 1 \cdot 1\]

\[= 32768 + 4096 + 3072 + 512 + 64 + 0 + 12 + 1\]

\[= 40401_{10}\]

### Adding the two base-10 numbers:

\[6214 + 40401 = 46615_{10}\]

### Converting the result back to base-4:

To convert \(46615_{10}\) back to base-4, we divide by increasing powers of 4 and take the remainders:

\[
\begin{array}{r|l}
46615 \div 4 = 11653 \quad \text{remainder} \; 3 \\
11653 \div 4 = 2913 \quad \text{remainder} \; 1 \\
2913 \div 4 = 728 \quad \text{remainder} \; 1 \\
728 \div 4 = 182 \quad \text{remainder} \; 0 \\
182 \div 4 = 45 \quad \text{remainder} \; 2 \\
45 \div 4 = 11 \quad \text{remainder} \; 1 \\
11 \div 4 = 2 \quad \text{remainder} \; 3 \\
2 \div 4 = 0 \quad \text{remainder} \; 2 \\
\end{array}
\]

Reading the remainders from bottom to top, the number \(46615_{10}\) in base-4 is:

\[23012113_4\]

### Summary:
\(1201012_4 + 21321031_4 = 6214_{10} + 40401_{10} = 46615_{10} = 23012113_4\)